Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da 'yan bindiga' tare da tallace-tallace
Mako guda bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta gudanar da tallace-tallace na shafukan hudu a cikin wani shafin Amurka na yau da kullum da ke nuna fa'idodin ciniki na Amurka-China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da yin amfani da manema labarai na Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaban kasar Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana a ranar Laraba da ya gabata game da karin kuɗin da aka biya a cikin Register Des Moines - jihar Iowa ta babbar jaridar - bayan ya zargi kasar Sin da kokarin shiga zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka na 6 ga watan Nuwamba, wanda ake zargi da kasar Sin.
zargin Trump cewa Beijing tana kokarin shiga zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka faɗa wa Reuters sabon mataki ne a cikin yakin da Washington ke tayar da hankali kan China.
Duk da yake yana da al'ada ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su sanya talla don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna kulle a cikin wani yakin kasuwanci wanda ya ga su matakin zagaye na haraji akan shigo da juna.
An tsara farashin farashin farashin kasar Sin a farkon yakin kasuwanci don buga masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi irin su Iowa wanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, masana kimiyyar Sin da Amurka sun ce.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin da tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayan aikin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikata, manoma da kasuwancin Amurka.
Kasar Sin, Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wani ra'ayi a cikin Register Des Moines na Lahadi, "Yanzu yana raguwa a kan wannan rikice-rikice ta hanyar gudanar da tallace-tallace a cikin 'yan jarida na 'yanci."
